{"id":"1210.4617","submitter":"My. Brahim Sedra","authors":"A. Belhaj, M. Chabab, H. El Moumni, M. B. Sedra","title":"On Thermodynamics of AdS Black Holes in Arbitrary Dimensions","comments":"8 pages, 10 figures, Accepted by Chin. Phys. Lett. on 18/9/2012","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1088/0256-307X/29/10/100401","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Considering the cosmological constant $\\Lambda$ as a thermodynamic pressure\nand its conjugate quantity as a thermodynamic volume as proposed in Kubiznak\nand Mann (2012), we discuss the critical behavior of charged AdS black hole in\narbitrary dimensions $d$. In particular, we present a comparative study in\nterms of the spacetime dimension $d$ and the displacement of critical points\ncontrolling the transition between the small and the large black holes. Such\nbehaviors vary nicely in terms of $d$. Among our result in this context\nconsists in showing that the equation of state for a charged RN-AdS black hole\npredicts an universal number given by $\\frac{2d-5}{4d-8}$. The three\ndimensional solution is also discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 23 Sep 2012 21:51:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-11"}
